A 37-year-old woman has been found dead in her car in Toekomsrus, Johannesburg, early morning of this Monday, November 14, Randfontein Herald reports. According to a close family member, her body was discovered at about 6am by another relative. The deceased woman is a mother of two children. The family member added that the Randfontein police were at the scene. READ MORE: Man found dead in car hanging over embankment When the Herald arrived, the family was waiting for a tow-truck to remove the vehicle. The family member further alleges that the deceased was out, fetching her child/children on Sunday night and never returned home. According to Captain Appel Ernst, the Randfontein police spokesperson, the police are busy with the investigation, and an official comment will follow as soon as possible. &#8211; Caxton News Service